Grammar

    0 $accept: input $end

    1 input: %empty
    2      | input line

    3 line: NEWLINE
    4     | expr NEWLINE

    5 expr: NUMBER
    6     | expr PLUS expr
    7     | expr MINUS expr
    8     | expr MUL expr
    9     | expr DIV expr


Terminals, with rules where they appear

    $end (0) 0
    error (256)
    NUMBER (258) 5
    PLUS (259) 6
    MINUS (260) 7
    MUL (261) 8
    DIV (262) 9
    NEWLINE (263) 3 4


Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

    $accept (9)
        on left: 0
    input (10)
        on left: 1 2
        on right: 0 2
    line (11)
        on left: 3 4
        on right: 2
    expr (12)
        on left: 5 6 7 8 9
        on right: 4 6 7 8 9


State 0

    0 $accept: . input $end

    $default  reduce using rule 1 (input)

    input  go to state 1


